message:
@Neilan The point about the 'unfinished code' is the ethics, I suppose. How can PC Gamer present a review of a game as if its the retail copy, when it isn't, and thats OK? Sure, you can argue that its not like the game is going to get worse, but the game they reviewed, and the game you and I will play is _not_ the same thing.

I suppose you can also argue Day 1 patches change the landscape of review code versus retail.

Regarding MW2, its a really good game for the second half of it, the first half is very pedestrian. MW1 was far superior insomuch that it wasn't so heavy-handed and overt.
